        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(subagent): reconcile child output before lost-context sweep",
        "body": "Fixes #90299\n\n## Problem\n\nThe lost-context sweep in `sweepSubagentRuns()` marks a subagent as `failed: subagent run lost active execution context` without first attempting to read the child's output. When the child produces output but the parent's run context is lost (e.g. process restart), this creates an inconsistent lifecycle state: the child completes successfully but the parent sees it as failed.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe sweep flow in `subagent-registry.ts` checks for orphaned runs and session-store completion, but when neither resolves, it immediately falls through to the \"lost active execution context\" error. It never tries to capture the child's actual output.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd an output reconciliation step in the sweep before the lost-context fallback:\n\n1. Call `captureSubagentCompletionReply()` to check if the child has produced output\n2. If output is found, complete the run with `status: \"ok\"` (source: `sweeper-output-reconciliation`)\n3. If no output is found or the capture throws, fall back to the original \"lost active execution context\" error\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/agents/subagent-registry.ts`**: Insert output reconciliation between the `abortedLastRun` guard and the lost-context error in `sweepSubagentRuns()`\n- **`src/agents/subagent-registry.test.ts`**: Add 3 regression tests:\n  - Reconciles child output before lost-context sweep marks run as failed\n  - Falls back to lost-context error when child has no output to reconcile\n  - Falls back to lost-context error when output capture throws",
        "branch": "fix/90299-subagent-lost-context-reconcile-output",
